    "narrative": "For the April 14th slate, our offensive anchor is undoubtedly **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez**, who commands an elite score of 76.15 against McGreevy. The combination of a favorable 4.57 xERA matchup and a wind-out advantage creates high upside for power production, making him the clear priority in the Utility slot. We also see high-efficiency output from **Geraldo Perdomo** (65.30) and **Matt Chapman** (63.93). **Geraldo Perdomo** is benefiting significantly from a 16% park factor boost, while **Matt Chapman** leverages a strong platoon advantage against Singer. Elsewhere, we are leaning into **Tyler Freeman** (61.79) and **Luis Arraez** (61.76) to stabilize our AVG floor, as both players project well above our threshold for consistent production today.\n\nThe most difficult decision on today's roster involved the final bench spots, where **Jonathan Aranda** was the primary candidate for promotion. Ultimately, his score of 48.85 was suppressed by a negative platoon shift against the left-handed Schultz and a 39% rain risk, which necessitated caution. We opted to stay with our current configuration, though we are monitoring the **Jonathan Aranda** situation closely should the weather report improve. While **Gleyber Torres** faces a formidable arm in Ragans (2.52 xERA), his leading-off position and strong platoon bias against lefties keep his floor high enough to warrant a start over the risk-heavy **Wenceel Perez** or **Masyn Winn**.\n\nRisk management remains a theme, particularly with **Gleyber Torres** and **Will Smith**, both of whom are battling sub-3.00 xERA arms today. **Will Smith**'s score of 51.88 is bolstered slightly by wind conditions, but he remains a volatile play against the efficiency of McLean. Furthermore, we are keeping a close watch on **Jeremiah Jackson**; while he sits lower in the order, his speed profile is critical for our SB goals, and his 87% stolen base success rate against the opposing battery keeps him relevant despite a marginal raw score of 55.61. We are confident that this lineup configuration maximizes our daily efficiency while navigating a challenging slate of opposing arms.",
